'''
log with timestamp
'''
def log(text):
    now_str = datetime.datetime.now().strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")
    print(f'{now_str}: {text}')
    
'''
randomly split the images into test, train, valid datasets
'''
def my_test_train_valid_splitter(img_folder, seed):
    full_n = len(os.listdir(img_folder))
    full_set = list(range(1,full_n+1))
    # set seed for reproducability
    random.seed(seed)
    # 80% of images go into training
    train_valid = random.sample(list(range(1,full_n+1)),int(.8*full_n))
    # remaining 20% go into test
    test = list(set(full_set)-set(train_valid))
    # reset seed for reproducibility
    random.seed(seed)
    # 80% of train_valid goes to train, remaining 20% goes to valid
    train = random.sample(train_valid, int(.8*len(train_valid)))
    valid = list(set(train_valid)-set(train))
    
    return (train,valid,test)

'''
manufacture the names of the image files based on index
'''
def get_names(_class,indices):
    file_names = [_class+str(i)+".jpg" for i in indices]
    return(file_names)

'''
bulk copy files
'''
def move_files(source_files, dest_folder):
    for file in source_files:
        shutil.copy(file, dest_folder)

'''
organize files per imagenet standard
'''
def organize(_class, file_indexes, source_folder, dest_folder):
    file_names = get_names(_class, file_indexes)
    source_file_paths = [os.path.join(source_folder, name) for name in file_names]
    train_dest = os.path.join(train_path, _class)
    move_files(source_file_paths, dest_folder)


'''
set up checkpointing to save the best model
'''
def get_model_checkpointer(run_type):
    model_checkpoint_file = f'{MODEL_TYPE}/model_checkpoints/{run_type}'

    checkpointer = K.callbacks.ModelCheckpoint(
        model_checkpoint_file, 
        monitor = 'val_acc', 
        verbose = 1, 
        save_best_only = True, 
        mode = 'max'
    )

    return checkpointer

'''
select the first file in the directory for testing
'''
def get_file_in_dir(directory, idx=0):
    for dirpath,_,filenames in os.walk(directory):
        #for f in filenames:
        return os.path.abspath(os.path.join(dirpath, filenames[idx]))

'''
bar chart to show classification probablility percentage for each class
on a single image
'''
def plot_probablility(classes, probabilities):
    idx = np.arange(len(classes))
    plt.bar(idx, probabilities)
    plt.xlabel('type')
    plt.ylabel('Probability')
    plt.ylim(0, 1)
    plt.xticks(idx, classes, rotation=20)
    plt.title('Waste Type Probability')
    plt.show()

'''
print directory structure
'''
def list_files(startpath):
    for root, dirs, files in os.walk(startpath):
        level = root.replace(startpath, '').count(os.sep)
        indent = ' ' * 4 * (level)
        print('{}{}/'.format(indent, os.path.basename(root)))
        subindent = ' ' * 4 * (level + 1)
        for f in files[:3]:
            print('{}{}'.format(subindent, f))
'''
query the keras tuner trial history for the best objective value
'''
def get_max_objective_for_trials(tuner, objective, index=0):
    #for trial in tuner.oracle.get_best_trials(num_trials=index+1)[index]:
    trial = tuner.oracle.get_best_trials(num_trials=index+1)[index]
    metrics_tracker = trial.metrics 
    metric_histories = metrics_tracker.metrics
    history = metric_histories[objective]
    objective_val = history.get_history()
    max_objective = max([o.value[0] for o in objective_val])
    #print(f'max {objective} for tuner: {max_objective}')
    return max_objective

'''
get the hyperparameters from the tuner
'''
def get_tuner_model_info(tuner, tuner_type, max_models=20):
    #[model_type, preprocess_rescale, preprocess_random_flip, batch_norm, dense_units, dropout_rate, learning_rate, tuner/epochs, tuner/initial_epoch, tuner/bracket, tuner/round]
    results = [] 
    models = tuner.get_best_models(num_models=max_models)
    hyperparams = tuner.get_best_hyperparameters(num_trials=max_models)
    for i in range(len(models)):
        
        _hyperparams = hyperparams[i]
        val_acc = get_max_objective_for_trials(tuner, 'val_acc', i)

        stats = [
            _hyperparams.get('model_type'),
            _hyperparams.get('preprocess_rescale'),
            _hyperparams.get('preprocess_random_flip'),
            _hyperparams.get('batch_norm'),
            _hyperparams.get('dense_units'),
            _hyperparams.get('dropout_rate'),
            _hyperparams.get('learning_rate'),
            tuner_type,
            val_acc
        ]
        results.append(stats)

    return results

'''
get timedelta in hours minutes seconds
'''
def format_timedelta(td):
    hours = td.seconds // 3600
    minutes = (td.seconds % 3600) // 60
    seconds = td.seconds % 60
    return f'hr: {hours}, min: {minutes}, sec: {seconds}'

Base CNN Model¶

In [9]:
def add_basecnn_layers_to_model(hp, model, input_shape):

    model.add(K.layers.Conv2D(32,(3,3), padding='same',input_shape=input_shape, activation='relu')), #32 output filters, 3 height, 3 width # https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/keras/layers/Conv2D
    model.add(K.layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=2)),
    model.add(K.layers.Conv2D(64,(3,3), padding='same',activation='relu')),
    model.add(K.layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=2)),
    model.add(K.layers.Conv2D(32,(3,3), padding='same',activation='relu')),
    model.add(K.layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=2)),

    return model

DenseNet121 Model¶

In [10]:
'''
build a densenet 121 layer model
using pre-trained weights and layers from imagenet
'''
def add_densenet121_layers_to_model(hp, model, input_shape):

    # get pre-trained model and weights for DenseNet121 from imagenet
    pretrained_model = K.applications.DenseNet121(
        include_top = False,
        input_shape = input_shape,
        pooling = 'avg',
        classes = num_classes,
        weights = 'imagenet'
    )

    # do not re-train pre-trained model layers
    for layer in pretrained_model.layers:
        layer.trainable = False

    # add all the layers to the new model
    model.add(pretrained_model)

    return model

In [13]:
class WasteClassifierHyperModel(kt.HyperModel):

    def build(self, hp):
        model_type = hp.Choice("model_type", MODEL_TYPES)
        
        model = K.Sequential()

        if hp.Boolean("preprocess_rescale"):
            model.add(K.layers.Rescaling(1./255))

        # vgg, densenet, resnet50 require 224x224 images, base cnn does not
        if model_type in ['vgg16', 'densenet121','resnet50']:
            img_height, img_width = 224, 224
        else:
            img_height, img_width = 300, 300
            
            
        input_shape = (img_height, img_width, IMG_DIMENSIONS)
        model.add(K.layers.Resizing(img_height, img_width))
        if hp.Boolean("preprocess_random_flip"):
            model.add(K.layers.RandomFlip())

        #model.add(K.layers.CategoryEncoding(num_tokens=num_classes, output_mode="one_hot"))

        if model_type == 'basecnn':
            model = add_basecnn_layers_to_model(hp, model, input_shape)
        elif model_type == 'densenet121':
            model = add_densenet121_layers_to_model(hp, model, input_shape)
        elif model_type == 'resnet50':
            model = add_resnet50_layers_to_model(hp, model, input_shape)
        elif model_type == 'vgg16':
            model = add_vgg16_layers_to_model(hp, model, input_shape)
        else:
            raise Exception(f'model_type: {model_type} is not supported!')

        # flatted input through 3 dense layers
        model.add(K.layers.Flatten())

        if hp.Boolean("batch_norm"):
            model.add(K.layers.BatchNormalization())

        model.add(K.layers.Dense(hp.Int('dense_units', min_value=32, max_value=256, step=32, default=128), activation='relu'))
        model.add(K.layers.Dropout(rate=hp.Float('dropout_rate',min_value=0.0,max_value=0.5,default=0.2,step=0.1)))
        
        # add a fully connected layer for the final classification
        model.add(K.layers.Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax'))

        #hp_learning_rate = hp.Float('learning_rate',min_value=1e-5,max_value=1e-2,sampling='LOG',default=1e-3)
        hp_learning_rate = hp.Choice('learning_rate', values = TUNING_LEARNING_RATES)
        model.compile(
            optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=hp_learning_rate),
            loss='categorical_crossentropy',
            metrics=['acc']
        )
        
        return model

# callback - do not continue with testing if the accuracy is not increasing after 5 epochs

    monitor = 'val_acc', 
    patience = EARLY_STOPPING_PATIENCE,
    restore_best_weights=True
)

cb_checkpointer = get_model_checkpointer('tuning')

# set up a keras tuner to find the best hyperparameters
# https://keras.io/guides/keras_tuner/getting_started/
hyperband_tuner = kt.Hyperband(
    hypermodel = WasteClassifierHyperModel(),
    objective = 'val_acc',
    max_epochs = TUNING_EPOCHS,
    project_name = 'hyperband_tuner',
    overwrite = True
)

# find the best model using all combinations of hyperparameters
hyperband_tuner.search(
    train_generator,
    steps_per_epoch = train_image_count // BATCH_SIZE,
    epochs = TUNING_EPOCHS,
    validation_data = validation_generator,
    validation_steps = valid_image_count // BATCH_SIZE,
    callbacks = [cb_early_stopper, K.callbacks.TensorBoard(hyperband_log_dir)],
    shuffle = False, # this allows for reproducible evaluate() stats
    verbose = 1, # to show lots of output
    initial_epoch = 0
)

# verify accuracy is correct
if True:
    hits = 0
    misses = 0
    for i in range(0,len(actual_class)):
        acutal_class_desc = classes[actual_class[i]]
        predicted_class_desc = classes[predicted_class[i]]

        if actual_class[i] == predicted_class[i]:
            hits += 1
        else:
            misses += 1
    accuracy = hits/len(actual_class)
    print(f'accuracy: {round(accuracy,4)}')

test predicting a single image¶

  • evaluate result of prediction against an image of each class
In [36]:
best_model_type = best_hyperparams.get('model_type')
for c in classes:
    
    # start timing the prediction
    starttime = timeit.default_timer()
    
    #load the image
    test_img_path = get_file_in_dir(os.path.join(test_path,c))
    target_size = (224, 224) if best_model_type not in ['basecnn'] else (300,300)
    raw_test_image = load_img(test_img_path, target_size=target_size)

    my_image = img_to_array(raw_test_image)
    my_image = np.expand_dims(my_image, axis=0)
    preprocessed_image = my_image

    #make the prediction
    prediction = best_model.predict(preprocessed_image)
    
    # end timing prediction
    time_to_predict = timeit.default_timer() - starttime
    
    individual_class_pcts = {}
    for i in range(0,len(prediction[0])):

        class_name = classes[i]
        predicted_pct = prediction[0][i]
        individual_class_pcts[class_name] = predicted_pct
        
    max_pct = np.max(prediction[0], axis=-1)
    formatted_max_pct = "{:07.4f} %".format(float(max_pct*100))
    predicted_class = classes[np.argmax(prediction[0], axis=-1)]
    
    print('\n------------------------------------------')
    print(f'test image path: {test_img_path}\n')
    print(f'  predicted [{predicted_class}]'.ljust(10))
    print(f'  actual    [{c}]'.ljust(10))
    print(f'    with probability: {formatted_max_pct}')
    
    plt.imshow(raw_test_image)
    plt.show()
    
    probabilities = [p for p in individual_class_pcts.values()]
    plot_probablility(classes, probabilities)
    print("\n  duration = {:.4f} seconds".format(time_to_predict) )
    
    print('\n  full prediction percentages\n')
    for c,p in individual_class_pcts.items():
        print(f'    {c}'.ljust(13) + ' =  ' + '{:07.4f}'.format(p*100))
